<title>USA: Trans-Lux Corp Q1 net increases.</title>
<headline>Trans-Lux Corp Q1 net increases.</headline>
<dateline>NORWALK, Conn. 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>THREE MONTHS ENDED</p>
<p>							  MARCH 31</p>
<p>						   1997	   1996</p>
<p> Revenues				$10,548,000  $10,033,000</p>
<p> Net income				  271,000	248,000</p>
<p> Earnings per share - primary	     0.21	   0.20</p>
<p> Earnings per share - fully diluted     0.20	   0.19</p>
<p>Average common shares</p>
<p> outstanding - primary		 1,298,000    1,263,000</p>
<p>Average common shares</p>
<p> outstanding - fully diluted	 3,755,000    1,647,000</p>
<p>NOTE:  Average shares outstanding - fully diluted assumes 2,214,000 shares upon conversion of $31,625,000 of the company's 7-1/2 percent Convertible Subordinated Notes due 2006.</p>
<p>Net income for the first quarter of 1997 included a charge of approximately $113,000, or $0.05 per share, for the unamortized portion of a call on its nine percent debentures.</p>
